{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"edef7b51-5ce2-422c-8b97-5e3ad3ffa539","content":"The change is straightforward. In your project file, remove (or set to `false`) the `UseVSTest` property:\n\n**Before:**\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**After:**\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — `MSTest.Sdk` 3.8+ uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform by default** when `UseVSTest` is not set (or is `false`).\n\n### Key differences to be aware of:\n\n1. **Test runner CLI** — Run with `dotnet test` as before, but the underlying runner changes. You can also run the test executable directly.\n2. **`--filter`** — Syntax stays the same, but the flag becomes `--filter` (no `=`) when invoking the exe directly.\n3. **Incompatible VSTest adapters** — If you reference any VSTest-specific `.runsettings` features or third-party VSTest adapters, verify they support Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n4. **CI output** — The default result format changes (TRX is still available via `--results-directory` / `--report-trx`). Add the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` package if you need TRX output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4c5959b8-d75d-4d65-b0f2-d1977f0acc2d","outputTokens":349,"requestId":"1BC0:349D35:205803E:23BCD3C:6A03CE7E"},"id":"ae717cbc-389d-450a-af72-f7a4d412bc84","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:06:16.565Z","parentId":"77fc5add-a223-4c00-bf54-34f3dce65903"}
